{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b33ec13-ea5b-40be-8352-6faaed34ba1a","content":"**No, the migration steps are different.** These projects are at different starting points:\n\n**LegacyTests** — MSTest **v1** (assembly reference to `QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`, targeting `net462`). This needs a two-stage migration:\n1. First migrate from v1 → v2/v3 (replace the assembly reference with NuGet packages, update the TFM to a supported one like `net8.0`).\n2. Then migrate from v3 → v4.\n\n**ModernTests** — MSTest **v2** (NuGet `MSTest.TestFramework` 2.2.10, targeting `net6.0`). This is already on NuGet packages, so the path is shorter:\n1. Update packages to v3 (and TFM to `net8.0`+ since `net6.0` is out of support).\n2. Then migrate from v3 → v4.\n\nThe `LegacyTests` project has the extra prerequisite of moving off the GAC assembly reference to NuGet-based packages before any version upgrade can happen.\n\nWould you like me to perform either (or both) migrations?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e0c913e0-cf3e-490f-8f54-020d4c1ccc36","outputTokens":273,"requestId":"23C9:3DF1E0:49825B:4EBA8E:6A03114B"},"id":"8f5a0baa-960f-4843-b5b3-87797f0b1c87","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:59.490Z","parentId":"e9b16946-4cce-4d66-afde-4f1834195dee"}
